Row reduce $A$ to echelon form, recording the multipliers:
$$
\begin{bmatrix} 2 & 4 & -1 \\ 4 & 9 & -3 \\ -2 & -3 & 7 \end{bmatrix}
&\xrightarrow{R_2 - 2R_1}
\begin{bmatrix} 2 & 4 & -1 \\ 0 & 1 & -1 \\ -2 & -3 & 7 \end{bmatrix}
\xrightarrow{R_3 + R_1}
\begin{bmatrix} 2 & 4 & -1 \\ 0 & 1 & -1 \\ 0 & 1 & 6 \end{bmatrix} \\
&\xrightarrow{R_3 - R_2}
\begin{bmatrix} 2 & 4 & -1 \\ 0 & 1 & -1 \\ 0 & 0 & 7 \end{bmatrix} = U
$$
The multipliers were $2$, $-1$, and $1$. Place them in $L$:
\[
L = \begin{bmatrix} 1 & 0 & 0 \\ 2 & 1 & 0 \\ -1 & 1 & 1 \end{bmatrix}, \quad
U = \begin{bmatrix} 2 & 4 & -1 \\ 0 & 1 & -1 \\ 0 & 0 & 7 \end{bmatrix}
\]
Verify: $LU = A$.
